# AI Hub - outputs folder layout

The repo-root `outputs/` folder collects every saved AI run from every
section. To keep it browsable when the user accumulates dozens of runs
across AI Career / AI Jobs / AI Finance / AI LinkedIn / future
sections, **every** call into `src.services.store.new_run_dir(...)` must
pass a `section=<section_key>` argument so the run lands in
`outputs/<section_key>/<run-slug>-<timestamp>/`.

## Disk layout (what the user sees)

```
outputs/
  ai_career/
    senior-qa-engineer-gen-20260516-141700/
        Tailored_CV.pdf
        Cover_Letter.pdf
        summary.json
        ...
  ai_jobs/
    qa-engineer-search-20260516-142200/
        results.html
        summary.json
  ai_finance/
    ai-finance-20260516-150100/
        Budget.pdf
        ...
  ai_linkedin/
    senior-qa-engineer-20260516-152000/
        14_full_linkedin_profile.html
        ...
```

The full top-level `outputs/` folder is git-ignored
(see [`.gitignore`](mdc:../../.gitignore) -> `outputs/`); the per-section
subfolders inherit that pattern automatically, so contributors do
**not** need to add new entries to `.gitignore` when introducing a new
section.

## Hard rules - never break these

1. **Every section that saves runs uses `section=<section_key>`.** Pass
 the same key that lives in `src/sections/<key>/` and is set in the
 ``key=`` field of the section's `section.py`. Do **not** invent a
 different name (no `ai-jobs` vs `ai_jobs`, no nicknames like
 `cv` for `ai_career`) - mirror the code identifier so debug logs
 and on-disk paths line up.

 ```python
 # src/sections/ai_jobs/pipeline.py
 run_dir = store.new_run_dir(
 role=STATE.last_query or "ai-jobs",
 company="search",
 section="ai_jobs", # mandatory
 )
 ```

2. **"Open outputs folder" buttons must open the per-section
 subfolder when it exists.** Use `store.section_runs_dir(<key>)` and
 fall back to `store.runs_dir()` only when the per-section folder
 hasn't been created yet (i.e. the user has never saved a run from
 this section).

 ```python
 section_root = str(store.section_runs_dir("ai_jobs"))
 target = (
 STATE.last_run_folder
 or (section_root if os.path.isdir(section_root) else str(store.runs_dir()))
 )
 ```

3. **Do not commit `outputs/`.** The folder is already in
 `.gitignore`. New section subfolders inherit this - no edit needed.

4. **Mandatory ERROR log when `new_run_dir` raises.** Wrap the call in
 try / except and use `log_exception("<section_key>.pipeline",
 "save_full_new_run_dir_failed", exc)` so the user sees why the
 save did not produce a folder. The store helper itself already
 logs `new_run_dir_section_missing` (WARNING) when contributors
 forget the `section=` kwarg, but it cannot recover from a missing
 disk / permission issue on its own.

## When you add a new section that saves

1. Pick the section key (mirrors the folder under `src/sections/<key>/`
 and the `key=` field in `section.py`).
2. Pass it as `section=<key>` to every `store.new_run_dir(...)` call.
3. Wire any "Open folder" button through `store.section_runs_dir(<key>)`.
4. Update both READMEs to mention the new path
 (`outputs/<section>/<run-slug>-<timestamp>/`); see
 [docs-and-license.mdc](mdc:docs-and-license.mdc).

## Backwards compatibility

Existing entries in `~/AI Hub/history.json` already point at absolute
paths like `outputs/qa-engineer-20260508-204231/` (the pre-subfolder
layout). They keep working untouched - the History tab uses the stored
absolute path, not a recomputed one. Only **new** runs land in the new
per-section subfolder; we never silently relocate the user's existing
runs.

## Don't

- Do **not** call `store.new_run_dir(...)` without `section=`. The
 store helper will still create a folder under the legacy
 top-level `outputs/`, but it logs a WARNING that contributors will
 see in the in-app debug log.
- Do **not** hard-code the path `outputs/<key>/`. Always go through
 `store.section_runs_dir(<key>)` so we keep one source of truth.
- Do **not** duplicate runs across two section folders. A run belongs
 to exactly one section.
